    "department": "Marketing \u0026 Design",
    "description": "WHAT WE DO\n\nGecko Robotics is helping the world’s most important organizations ensure the availability, reliability, and sustainability of critical infrastructure. Gecko's complete and connected solutions combine wall-climbing robots, industry-leading sensors, and an AI-powered data platform to provide customers with a unique window into the current and future health of their physical assets. This enables real-time decision making to increase the efficiency and safety of operations, promote mission readiness, and protect the environment and civilization from the effects of infrastructure failure.\n\n\nROLE AT A GLANCE\n\nAs a Motion Designer at Gecko Robotics, you will be the bridge between static design and cinematic storytelling. We are looking for a \"Graphic Designer with an innate sense of pacing and rhythm.” Someone with a relentless eye for taste, composition, and technical detail. You won’t just be \"creating graphics\"; you’ll be defining how our brand feels in motion, from animating interfaces to creating 3D overlays on industrial robotics footage. You are a go-getter who thrives in a fast-paced environment and is obsessed with the future of AI \u0026 Robotics. We hope you can join us for a 10-15 week internship in Pittsburgh, PA.\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL DO\n\n - Motion Branding: Transform static campaign visuals into living, moving works using a catalogue of cinematic robot footage and cutting edge software interfaces, from around the world of critical infrastructure.\n\n - Post-Production Polish: Collaborate with the Videographer to enhance footage with technical overlays, motion-tracked graphics, and 2D/3D elements. The end result is not just cool- it connects Gecko’s capabilities with direct impacts to the world.\n\n - Software Visualization: Create compelling \"product-in-action\" advertisements by animating our software UI to demonstrate value and functionality.\n\n - Full-Spectrum Design: Execute high-end 2D graphic design for diverse assets including brand ads, event posters, and presentation decks.\n\n - 3D Integration: Render 3D models and assets to animate the breadth and depth of our robotic and software systems.\n\n - Rapid Prototyping: Conceptualize and storyboard ideas quickly, moving from a rough brief to a polished output with minimal oversight.\n\n - Team: Embedded in a tight-knit powerhouse team with wide ranging skillsets and opportunities to experience all sides of the business. Resources at your disposal from powerful workstations to experts in their field.\n\n\nABOUT YOU\n\n - Education: You are studying Motion Design, Graphic Design, or similar curriculum.\n\n - Design-First: A background in Graphic Design. You understand typography, grid systems, and color theory as the foundation of great visual communication.\n\n - Taste: A portfolio that demonstrates a clean, straightforward, and technical aesthetic. You know how to craft complex ideas into compelling media.\n\n - Self-Starter: You don't wait for a storyboard; you come up with one. You are comfortable working quickly and iterating based on technical feedback.\n\n - Experience: Comfortable creating across a wide range of mediums, demonstrated with a diverse body of work.\n\n - Must Have: Proficiency in After Effects and the Adobe Creative Suite, DaVinci for Video Editing, Figma for UI/UX motion.\n\n - Nice to Have: 3D software Proficiency (Blender, Octane, Redshift, Cinema 4D, Keyshot). Experience creating motion design for web experiences.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
